Modified continuous performance test (m-CPT) - ideated by : Amicuzi, P. 2022

This task allow to measure substained attention (i.e. vigilance) using different letters with different colors. This also allow to reveal also other index using some distractors (i.e. similar letters). We advise to assess the absence of dyslexia or visual color impairments before in order to have clean and not biases datas.

References:

Assessing attention functions [Riccio, C. A., Reynolds, C. R., Lowe, P., & Moore, J. J. (2002). The continuous performance test: A window on the neural substrates for attention? Archives of Clinical Neuropsychology, 17(3), 235â€“272.] 
